2.Which of the following is a difference between a class and an instance?
Choose as many answers as you see fit.


a)You can think of a class as a blueprint and an instance as the actual “thing".

b)A class is like architectural plans for a bridge, and the Golden Gate bridge an instance of those plans.

c)A class is for defining categories of "things", while instances are for defining their properties.

d)You can create multiple instances from a class, but you can't create classes from instances.

